On Wed, Mar 10, 1999 at 12:17:08PM -0500, Jonathan P Tomer wrote:

> my system just upgraded from zsh 3.0.5 to zsh 3.1.2 and i'm wondering if
> there is any way to turn off the new 'feature' that completion lists are 
> printed below the current prompt rather than redisplaying the prompt again 
> after a list. it's not listed anywhere in the docs and it drives me nuts :)

	setopt no_always_last_prompt

	-- sweth.

